<P STYLE="font: bold 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center">MASTER
PROMISSORY NOTE</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 48%; padding-right: 0; padding-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 0; font-weight: bold">$25,000,000</TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 52%; padding-right: 0; padding-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 0; text-align: right">February 2, 2009</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 12pt 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">FOR VALUE RECEIVED, the undersigned<FONT STYLE="color: black">,
MIDDLESEX WATER COMPANY</FONT>, <FONT STYLE="color: black">a New Jersey corporation (the &ldquo;<U>Borrower</U>&rdquo;), hereby
promises to pay to the order of BANK<B> </B>OF AMERICA, N.A. (the &ldquo;<U>Lender</U></FONT>&rdquo;), at its office at 750 Walnut
Avenue, Cranford, New Jersey 07016 (or at such other place as the Lender may designate from time to time), in lawful money of the
United States of America and in immediately available funds, the principal amount of Twenty Five Million Dollars ($25,000,000)
or such lesser amount as shall equal the aggregate unpaid principal amount of the advances (the &ldquo;<U>Loans</U>&rdquo;) made
by the Lender to the Borrower under this Master Promissory Note (this &ldquo;<U>Note</U>&rdquo;), and to pay interest on the unpaid
principal amount of each such Loan at the rates per annum and on the dates specified below.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">Each Loan hereunder shall be at the
sole discretion of the Lender. Each Loan shall have a maturity date and shall bear interest at the rate per annum quoted to the
Borrower by the Lender and accepted by the Borrower prior to the making of such Loan (which acceptance shall in any event be deemed
to occur upon receipt by the Borrower of the proceeds of any Loan). Each Loan, and accrued and unpaid interest thereon, shall be
due and payable, on the earlier of (a) the maturity date of such Loan, or (b) May 30, 2010 (&ldquo;Maturity Date&rdquo;). No Loan
shall have a maturity of more <FONT STYLE="color: black">than ninety (90) days or three months (whichever is longer) after the
date made. No Lo</FONT>an shall have a maturity beyond the Maturity Date. The Lender may, if and to the extent any payment is not
made when due hereunder, charge from time to time against any or all of the Borrower&rsquo;s accounts with the Lender any amount
so due.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">The date, amount, interest rate,
and maturity date of each Loan, and each payment of principal and interest hereon, shall be recorded by the Lender on its books,
which recordations shall, in the absence of manifest error, be conclusive as to such matters; <U>provided</U> that the failure
of the Lender to make any such recordation or any error therein shall not limit or otherwise affect the obligations of the Borrower
hereunder.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">The Borrower may not prepay any Loan
in whole or in part without the Lender&rsquo;s prior written consent; <U>provided</U>, <U>however</U>, that if any such prepayment
is made the Borrower shall at the time of prepayment compensate the Lender for any loss, cost, or expense that the Lender incurs
as a result of such prepayment. In addition, the Borrower shall compensate the Lender for any loss, cost or expense that the Lender
incurs as a result of a prepayment by reason of acceleration of the indebtedness hereunder.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">Interest shall be computed on the
basis of a year of 360 days and the actual days elapsed (including the first day but excluding the last day). Overdue principal
and, to the extent permitted by applicable law, interest shall bear interest, payable upon demand, for each day from and including
the due date to but excluding the date of actual payment at a rate per annum equal to the sum of 2% plus the rate of interest publicly
announced by the Lender from time to time as its prime rate. The Lender&rsquo;s prime rate is a rate set by the Lender based upon
various factors including the Lender&rsquo;s costs and desired return, general economic conditions and other factors, and is used
as a reference point for pricing some loans, which may be priced at, above, or below such announced rate. Whenever any payment
under this Note is due on a day that is not a day the Lender is open to conduct substantially all of its business, such payment
shall be made on the next succeeding day on which the Lender is open to conduct substantially all of its business, and such extension
of time shall in such case be included in the computation of the payment of interest.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">Each of the following shall constitute
an Event of Default hereunder: (a) the Borrower shall fail to pay when due any principal of or interest on any Loan; (b) a default
or event of default shall occur under the terms of any other indebtedness for which the Borrower or any of its subsidiaries is
liable, whether as principal obligor, guarantor, or otherwise <FONT STYLE="color: black">having an aggregate principal amount (including
undrawn committed or available amounts and including amounts owing to all creditors under any combined or syndicated credit arrangement)
in excess of $10,000,000;</FONT> (c) any representation, warranty, certification, or statement made or deemed made by the Borrower
to the Lender shall prove to have been incorrect or misleading in any material respect; (d) the Borrower shall dissolve, liquidate,
or terminate its legal existence or shall convey, transfer, lease, or dispose of (whether in one transaction or a series of transactions)
all or substantially all of its assets to any person or entity; (e) a petition shall be filed by or against the Borrower or any
of its subsidiaries under any law relating to bankruptcy, reorganization, or insolvency, or (f) the Borrower or any of its subsidiaries
shall make an assignment for the benefit of creditors or fail generally to pay its debts as they become due, or a receiver, trustee,
or similar official shall be appointed over the Borrower or any of its subsidiaries or a substantial portion of any of their respective
assets. If an Event of Default shall have occurred and be continuing, the Lender may declare the outstanding principal of and accrued
and unpaid interest on this Note, together with all other amounts payable hereunder, to be immediately due and payable without
presentment, protest, demand, or other notice of any kind, all of which are hereby waived by the Borrower; <U>provided</U>, <U>however</U>,
that upon the occurrence with respect to the Borrower of any event specified in clause (e) of the preceding sentence, the outstanding
principal and accrued and unpaid interest on this Note, together with all other amounts payable hereunder, shall become immediately
due and payable without presentment, protest, demand, or other notice of any kind, all of which are hereby waived by the Borrower.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 5 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 2px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->
<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">The request of the Borrower for any
Loan and the receipt by the Borrower of the proceeds thereof shall be deemed a representation by the Borrower as of the date of
each such request or receipt that no Event of Default has occurred and that the Borrower is duly authorized to incur such indebtedness
hereunder.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">No failure or delay by the Lender
in exercising, and no course of dealing with respect to, any right, power, or privilege hereunder shall operate as a waiver thereof
nor shall any single or partial exercise of any right, power, or privilege hereunder preclude any other or further exercise thereof
or the exercise of any other right, power, or privilege. The rights and remedies of the Lender provided herein shall be cumulative
and not exclusive of any other rights or remedies provided by law. If any provision of this Note shall be held invalid or unenforceable
in whole or in part, such invalidity or unenforceability shall not affect the remaining provisions hereof. No provision of this
Note may be modified or waived except by a written instrument signed by the Lender and the Borrower.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">The Lender shall incur no liability
to the Borrower in acting upon any telephone, telex, or other communication that the Lender in good faith believes has been given
by an authorized representative of the Borrower.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">The Lender may assign to one or more
banks or other entities all or any part of, or may grant participations to one or more banks or other entities in or to all or
any part of, this Note or any Loan or Loans hereunder.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">The Borrower shall pay on demand
all costs and expenses (including reasonable attorneys&rsquo; fees and the allocated costs of internal counsel) incurred by the
Lender in connection with any Event of Default or the enforcement or attempted enforcement of this Note.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">Notwithstanding anything to the contrary
contained herein, the interest paid or agreed to be paid hereunder shall not exceed the maximum rate of non-usurious interest permitted
by applicable law (the &ldquo;<U>Maximum Rate</U>&rdquo;). If the Lender shall receive interest in an amount that exceeds the Maximum
Rate, the excessive interest shall be applied to the principal of this Note or, if it exceeds the unpaid principal, refunded to
the Borrower. In determining whether the interest contracted for, charged, or received by the Lender exceeds the Maximum Rate,
the Lender may, to the extent permitted by applicable law, (a) characterize any payment that is not principal as an expense, fee,
or premium rather than interest, (b) exclude voluntary prepayments and the effects thereof, and (c) amortize, prorate, allocate,
and spread in equal or unequal parts the total amount of interest throughout the stated term of this Note.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">This Note shall be governed by and
construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New Jersey. The Borrower hereby submits to the nonexclusive jurisdiction
of the United States District Court and each state court in New Jersey as determined appropriate by the Lender for the purposes
of all legal proceedings arising out of or relating to this Note. The Borrower irrevocably waives, to the fullest extent permitted
by law, any objection that it may now or hereafter have to the laying of venue of any such proceeding brought in such a court and
any claim that any such proceeding brought in such a court has been brought in an inconvenient forum. The Borrower and the Lender
by acceptance of this Note hereby irrevocably waive any and all right to trial by jury in any legal proceeding arising out of or
relating to this Note.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 6 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 2px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->
<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/115% Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 6pt; text-indent: 0.5in">THIS NOTE AND ANY OTHER DOCUMENTS
EXECUTED IN CONNECTION HEREWITH REPRESENT THE FINAL AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE PARTIES AND MAY NOT BE CONTRADICTED BY EVIDENCE OF PRIOR,
CONTEMPORANEOUS, OR SUBSEQUENT ORAL AGREEMENTS OF THE PARTIES. THERE ARE NO UNWRITTEN ORAL AGREEMENTS BETWEEN THE PARTIES.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: right">Exhibit 10.39</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: right"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="image_007.jpg" ALT=""></P>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt/normal Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0"><B>Global Commercial Banking</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3.5in; text-indent: 0.5in">May 25, 2011</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3.5in; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">Utility Service Affiliates (Perth Amboy) Inc.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">1500 Ronson Road</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">Iselin, New Jersey 08830</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">Attention: Mr. Bruce O'Connor, Vice President and Chief Financial
Officer</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">Re: Extension of Maturity Date</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">Dear Mr. O'Connor:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">Reference is made to the Master Promissory
Note, dated July 18, 2008 (the &quot;Note&quot;) in the original maximum principal amount of Three Million and 00/100 Dollars ($3,000,000),
executed by Utility Service Affiliates (Perth Amboy) Inc., a New Jersey corporation (the &quot;Borrower&quot;) and delivered to
Bank of America, N.A. (the &quot;Bank&quot;), and the Uncommitted Line of Credit Letter Agreement, dated May 1, 2008, between the
Borrower and Bank (the &quot;Letter Agreement&rdquo;). The obligations to the Bank are guaranteed by Middlesex Water Company (the
&ldquo;Guarantor&rdquo;) under Continuing and Unconditional Guaranty, dated July 22, 2008 (the &ldquo;Guaranty&rdquo;). The Note,
Letter Agreement, Guaranty, and any and all other documents, instruments, and agreements executed in connection therewith are referred
to herein as the &quot;Loan Documents&quot;. Capitalized terms used herein shall have the meaning ascribed to them in the Loan
Documents.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">The Borrower has requested that the
Note, the Letter Agreement, and alI documents, instruments, agreements and amendments that evidence, govern or secure the Note
(together with the Note, and the Loan Documents) be modified for the purpose of extending the Maturity Date (as such term is defined
in the Loan Documents) and the Bank has agreed to such extension.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">The Bank agrees that the Maturity Date
as set forth in the Loan Documents shalI be extended from May 30, 2011 to May 30, 2012.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">Upon (a) the execution and
delivery of this Letter Agreement by the Borrower and (b) receipt by the Bank of any unpaid payments under the Loan
Documents, if any, through but not including the date of the execution and delivery of this letter and the extension set
forth in this letter shall be effective and enforceable against the Borrower and Guarantor. Nothing herein contained or
implied shalI be construed as a waiver of any other provision of the Loan Documents or any other document executed in
connection with the Loan Documents or a waiver of any presently existing or future default in the non-payment of principal
and/or interest or any other amounts due under the Loan Documents.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/13pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12pt; margin-left: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 32.1pt"></P>

<!-- Field: Rule-Page --><DIV ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="margin-top: 3pt; margin-bottom: 3pt"><DIV STYLE="font-size: 1pt; border-top: Black 1pt solid; width: 100%">&nbsp;</DIV></DIV><!-- Field: /Rule-Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 8pt/13pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12pt; margin-left: 0; text-align: right; text-indent: 32.1pt">Bank
of America, N.A., NJ6-502-03-08<BR>
750 Walnut Avenue, Cranford, NJ 07016</P>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt/13pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12pt; margin-left: 0; text-align: right; text-indent: 32.1pt">Member FDIC</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 4.5in; text-align: right"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 1 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 2px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->
<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 4.5in; text-align: right">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 4.5in; text-align: right">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: right">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">Each of the Borrower and the Guarantor
hereby warrants and represents that the representations and warranties contained in the Loan Documents continue to be true and
correct and that no event of default, and no event which with the giving of notice or lapse of time or both would become an event
of default, has occurred or is continuing under the Loan Documents. The Borrower acknowledges that as of the date hereof there
are no offsets, defenses, claims, counterclaims, charges or deductions of any nature against amounts due and owing under the Note
or against the Bank or any of its officers, directors or employers.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">The Borrower and the Guarantor hereby
ratify and confirm all respects and without condition all of the terms and provisions of the Loan Documents, as modified herein,
as applicable, and each agrees that said terms and provisions, except to the extent expressly modified herein, continue in full
force and effect.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">This letter shall be binding upon
the Borrower and each endorser and guarantor of the Loan Documents (including the Guarantor) and their respective successors,
heirs and assigns and shall inure to the benefit of the Bank and its successors and assigns. This Agreement shall take effect
as a sealed instrument and shall be governed by the laws of the State of New Jersey.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">In no event shall this letter
agreement constitute or be construed as a waiver or release of the obligations of any maker, guarantor, endorser or other
person liable for the Borrower's obligations under the Note, and the obligations of such parties shall remain in full force
and effect.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">If this letter extending the Maturity
Date is acceptable, please acknowledge below and return the acknowledged copy to me.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in">If you have any questions, please contact
me.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3in; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3in; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3in; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3in; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt/normal Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3in; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

that:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: left">&nbsp;</P>

    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">I have reviewed this Annual Report on Form 10-K of Middlesex Water Company;</FONT></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: left">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 10pt">

    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit
to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were
made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: left">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">

    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this
report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant
as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: left">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">

    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The registrant&rsquo;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining

reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and have;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: left">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 10pt">
    <TD STYLE="width: 0.75in; font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 0.5in; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">a)</FONT><FONT STYLE="font: 7pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures
to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated
subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being
prepared;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: left">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 10pt">
    <TD STYLE="width: 0.75in; font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 0.5in; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">b)</FONT><FONT STYLE="font: 7pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial
reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting
and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;</FONT></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font: bold 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">SECTION 906 CERTIFICATION PURSUANT TO 18
U.S.C. &sect;1350</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">I, Dennis W. Doll, hereby certify that, to
the best of my knowledge, the periodic report being filed herewith containing financial statements fully complies with the requirements
of section 13(a) or 15(d) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (15 U.S.C. 78m(a) or 78o(d)) and that information contained in
said periodic report fairly presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of operations of Middlesex
Water Company for the period covered by said periodic report.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: right"><B>Exhibit 32.1</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><B>SECTION 906 CERTIFICATION PURSUANT TO 18
U.S.C. &sect;1350</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 12pt 0 3pt; text-align: justify">I, A. Bruce O&rsquo;Connor, hereby
certify that, to the best of my knowledge, the periodic report being filed herewith containing financial statements fully complies
with the requirements of section 13(a) or 15(d) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (15 U.S.C. 78m(a) or 78o(d)) and that information
contained in said periodic report fairly presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of operations
of Middlesex Water Company for the period covered by said periodic report.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: bottom"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;/table&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;The statutory review periods for income tax returns for the&#13;years prior to 2009 have been closed. An examination by the Internal Revenue Service of Middlesex&amp;#146;s Federal income tax returns&#13;for 2007 and 2008 was completed during 2010 and resulted in a net refund, including interest, of less than $0.1 million. The refund&#13;noted above was recorded to the appropriate current and deferred tax accounts and the interest was reported as other income. In&#13;the event that there are interest and penalties associated with income tax adjustments in future examinations, these amounts will&#13;be reported under interest expense and other expense, respectively. There are no unrecognized tax benefits resulting from prior&#13;period tax positions. The Company is not aware of any uncertain tax positions that could result in a future tax liability.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Deferred income taxes reflect the net&#13;tax effect of temporary differences between the carrying amounts of assets and liabilities for financial purposes and the amounts&#13;used for income tax purposes.     <us-gaap:CommitmentsAndContingenciesDisclosureTextBlock contextRef="From2011-01-01to2011-12-31">&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note 4 - Commitments and Contingent&#13;Liabilities&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Water Supply&lt;/i&gt; - Middlesex has an&#13;agreement with the NJWSA for the purchase of untreated water through November 30, 2023, which provides for an average purchase&#13;of 27 million gallons a day (mgd). Pricing is set annually by the NJWSA through a public rate making process. The agreement has&#13;provisions for additional pricing in the event Middlesex overdrafts or exceeds certain monthly and annual thresholds.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Middlesex also has an agreement with a&#13;non-affiliated regulated water utility for the purchase of treated water. This agreement, which expires February 27, 2016, provides&#13;for the minimum purchase of 3 mgd of treated water with provisions for additional purchases.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Purchased water costs are shown below:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif;    &lt;td style="border-bottom: Black 2.5pt double; text-align: left"&gt;$&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="border-bottom: Black 2.5pt double; text-align: right"&gt;5.1&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="padding-bottom: 2.5pt; text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="padding-bottom: 2.5pt"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="border-bottom: Black 2.5pt double; text-align: left"&gt;$&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="border-bottom: Black 2.5pt double; text-align: right"&gt;5.4&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="padding-bottom: 2.5pt; text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="padding-bottom: 2.5pt"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="border-bottom: Black 2.5pt double; text-align: left"&gt;$&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="border-bottom: Black 2.5pt double; text-align: right"&gt;5.0&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style="padding-bottom: 2.5pt; text-align: left"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;/table&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Contract Operations - &lt;/i&gt;USA-PA operates&#13;the City of Perth Amboy, NJ&amp;#146;s water and wastewater systems under a 20-year agreement, which expires in 2018. In connection&#13;with the agreement with Perth Amboy, USA-PA entered into a 20-year subcontract with a wastewater operating company for the operation&#13;and maintenance of the Perth Amboy wastewater collection system. The subcontract provides for the sharing of certain fixed and&#13;variable fees and operating expenses.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Construction&lt;/i&gt; &amp;#150;The Company may&#13;spend up to $21.8 million in 2012, $18.0 million in 2013 and $16.4 million in 2014 on its construction program. The actual amount&#13;and timing of capital expenditures is dependent on customer growth, residential new home construction and sales and project scheduling.&#13;There is no assurance that projected customer growth and residential new home construction and sales will occur.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Litigation&lt;/i&gt; &amp;#150; The Company is a&#13;defendant in lawsuits in the normal course of business. We believe the resolution of pending claims and legal proceedings will&#13;not have a material adverse effect on the Company&amp;#146;s consolidated financial statements.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Change in Control Agreements &amp;#150;&#13;The Company has Change in Control Agreements with certain of its officers that provide compensation and benefits in the event of&#13;termination of employment in connection with a change in control of the Company.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:CommitmentsAndContingenciesDisclosureTextBlock>
    <us-gaap:SegmentReportingDisclosureTextBlock contextRef="From2011-01-01to2011-12-31">&lt;p style="font: bold 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 12pt 0 3pt; text-align: justify"&gt;Note 8 &amp;#150; Business Segment&#13;Data&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;The Company has identified two reportable segments.&#13;One is the regulated business of collecting, treating and distributing water on a retail and wholesale basis to residential, commercial,&#13;industrial and fire protection customers in parts of New Jersey, Delaware and Pennsylvania. This segment also includes regulated&#13;wastewater systems in New Jersey and Delaware. The Company is subject to regulations as to its rates, services and other matters&#13;by the states of New Jersey, Delaware and Pennsylvania with respect to utility service within these states. The other segment is&#13;primarily comprised of non-regulated contract services for the operation and maintenance of municipal and private water and wastewater&#13;systems in New Jersey and Delaware.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Inter-segment transactions relating to operational&#13;costs are treated as pass-through expenses. Finance charges on inter-segment loan activities are based on interest rates that are&#13;below what would normally be charged by a third party lender.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 3.5in; text-indent: 0.5in"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%;     <us-gaap:OrganizationConsolidationAndPresentationOfFinancialStatementsDisclosureAndSignificantAccountingPoliciesTextBlock contextRef="From2011-01-01to2011-12-31">&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note 1 &amp;#150; Organization, Summary of Significant Accounting&#13;Policies and Recent Developments&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(a)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Organization&lt;/b&gt; - Middlesex&#13;Water Company (Middlesex) is the parent company and sole shareholder of Tidewater Utilities, Inc. (Tidewater), Tidewater Environmental&#13;Services, Inc. (TESI), Pinelands Water Company (Pinelands Water) and Pinelands Wastewater Company (Pinelands Wastewater) (collectively,&#13;Pinelands), Utility Service Affiliates, Inc. (USA), Utility Service Affiliates (Perth Amboy) Inc. (USA-PA) and Twin Lakes Utilities,&#13;Inc. (Twin Lakes). Southern Shores Water Company, LLC (Southern Shores) and White Marsh Environmental Systems, Inc. (White Marsh)&#13;are wholly-owned subsidiaries of Tidewater. The financial statements for Middlesex and its wholly-owned subsidiaries (the Company)&#13;are reported on a consolidated basis. All significant intercompany accounts and transactions have been eliminated.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Middlesex Water Company has operated as a water&#13;utility in New Jersey since 1897, in Delaware, through our wholly-owned subsidiary, Tidewater, since 1992 and in Pennsylvania,&#13;through our wholly-owned subsidiary, Twin Lakes, since 2009. We are in the business of collecting, treating, distributing and selling&#13;water for domestic, commercial, municipal, industrial and fire protection purposes. We also operate a New Jersey municipal water&#13;and wastewater system under contract and provide wastewater services in New Jersey and Delaware through our subsidiaries. Our rates&#13;charged to customers for water and wastewater services, the quality of services we provide and certain other matters are regulated&#13;in New Jersey, Delaware and Pennsylvania by the New Jersey Board of Public Utilities (NJBPU), Delaware Public Service Commission&#13;(DEPSC) and Pennsylvania Public Utilities Commission (PAPUC), respectively. Only our USA, USA-PA and White Marsh subsidiaries are&#13;not regulated utilities.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Certain reclassifications have been made&#13;to the prior year financial statements to conform with current period presentation.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(b)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;System of Accounts&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;&amp;#150;&#13;&lt;/i&gt;Middlesex, Pinelands Water and Pinelands Wastewater maintain their accounts in accordance with the Uniform System of Accounts&#13;prescribed by the NJBPU. Tidewater, TESI and Southern Shores maintain their accounts in accordance with DEPSC requirements. Twin&#13;Lakes maintains its accounts in accordance with PAPUC requirements.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(c)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Utility Plant&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;&amp;#150;&#13;&lt;/i&gt;Utility Plant is stated at original cost as defined for regulatory purposes. Property accounts are charged with the cost of&#13;betterments and major replacements of property. Cost includes direct material, labor and indirect charges for pension benefits&#13;and payroll taxes. The cost of labor, materials, supervision and other expenses incurred in making repairs and minor replacements&#13;and in maintaining the properties is charged to the appropriate expense accounts. At December 31, 2011, there was no event or change&#13;in circumstance that would indicate that the carrying amount of any long-lived asset was not recoverable.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(d)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Depreciation &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;#150;&lt;/i&gt;&#13;Depreciation is computed by each regulated member of the Company utilizing a rate approved by the applicable regulatory&#13;authority. The Accumulated Provision for Depreciation is charged with the cost of property retired, less salvage. The&#13;following table sets forth the range of depreciation rates for the major utility plant categories used to calculate&#13;depreciation for the years ended December 31, 2011, 2010 and 2009. These rates have been approved by the NJBPU, DEPSC or&#13;PAPUC:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0 0 0 0.5in"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 80%; margin-left: 0; border-collapse: collapse"&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(204,238,255)"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;Source of Supply&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;1.15% -&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 3.44%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td colspan="2" style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;Transmission and Distribution (T&amp;#38;D):&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: top; background-color: White"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="width: 21%; padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;Pumping&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="width: 31%; padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;2.87% -&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 5.39%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="width: 22%; padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;T&amp;#38;D &amp;#150; Mains&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="width: 26%; padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;1.10%&amp;#160; -&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 3.13%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(204,238,255)"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;Water Treatment&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;1.65% -&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 7.09%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;T&amp;#38;D &amp;#150; Services&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;2.12%&amp;#160; -&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 3.16%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: top; background-color: White"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;General Plant&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;2.08% - 17.84%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;T&amp;#38;D &amp;#150; Other&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="padding-right: 5.4pt; padding-left: 5.4pt"&gt;1.61%&amp;#160; -&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 4.63%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;/table&gt;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Non-regulated fixed assets consist primarily&#13;of office buildings, furniture and fixtures, and transportation equipment. These assets are recorded at original cost and depreciation&#13;is calculated based on the estimated useful lives, ranging from 3 to 40 years.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(e)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Preliminary Survey and Investigation&#13;(PS&amp;#38;I)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Costs &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;#150; &lt;/i&gt;In the design of water and wastewater systems that the Company ultimately intends to&#13;construct, own and operate certain expenditures are incurred to advance those project activities. These PS&amp;#38;I costs are recorded&#13;as deferred charges on the balance sheet because these costs are expected to be recovered through future rates charged to customers&#13;as the underlying projects are placed into service as utility plant. If it is subsequently determined that costs for a project&#13;recorded as PS&amp;#38;I are not recoverable through rates charged to our customers, the applicable PS&amp;#38;I costs are recorded as&#13;a charge to the income statement at that time.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(f)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt; &lt;/i&gt;&lt;b&gt;Customers&amp;#146;&#13;Advances for Construction (CAC)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt; &amp;#150; &lt;/i&gt;Water utility plant and/or cash advances are contributed to the Company by&#13;customers, real estate developers and builders in order to extend water service to their properties. These contributions are&#13;recorded as CAC. Refunds on these advances are made by the Company in accordance with agreements with the contributing party&#13;and are based on either additional operating revenues related to the utility plant or as new customers are connected to and&#13;take service from the utility plant. After all refunds are made and/or contract terms have expired, any remaining balance&#13;is transferred to Contributions in Aid of Construction.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Contributions in Aid of Construction&lt;/b&gt;&#13;&lt;b&gt;(CIAC)&lt;/b&gt; &amp;#150; CIAC include direct non-refundable contributions of water utility plant and/or cash and the portion of CAC&#13;that becomes non-refundable.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;CAC and CIAC are not depreciated in accordance&#13;with regulatory requirements. In addition, these amounts reduce the investment base for purposes of setting rates.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(g)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Allowance for Funds Used&#13;During Construction (AFUDC)&lt;/b&gt; - Middlesex and its regulated subsidiaries capitalize AFUDC, which represents the cost of financing&#13;projects during construction. AFUDC is added to the construction costs of individual projects exceeding specific cost and construction&#13;period thresholds established for each company and then depreciated along with the rest of the utility plant&amp;#146;s costs over&#13;its estimated useful life. For the years ended December 31, 2011, 2010 and 2009, approximately $0.8 million, $1.0 million, and&#13;$1.0 million, respectively of AFUDC was added to the cost of construction projects. AFUDC is calculated using each company&amp;#146;s&#13;weighted cost of debt and equity as approved in their most recent respective regulatory rate order. The AFUDC rates for the years&#13;ended December 31, 2011, 2010 and 2009 for Middlesex and Tidewater are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" align="center" style="width: 40%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: bottom"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td colspan="3" style="text-align: center"&gt;For The Year Ended December 31,&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: bottom"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="width: 59pt; border-bottom: windowtext 0.5pt solid; text-align: center"&gt;2011&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="width: 59pt; border-bottom: windowtext 0.5pt solid; text-align: center"&gt;2010&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="width: 59pt; border-bottom: windowtext 0.5pt solid; text-align: center"&gt;2009&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: bottom; background-color: rgb(204,238,255)"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td&gt;Middlesex&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;7.54%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;7.54%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;7.65%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;tr style="vertical-align: bottom; background-color: White"&gt;&#13;    &lt;td&gt;Tidewater&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;8.24%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;8.24%&lt;/td&gt;&#13;    &lt;td style="text-align: right"&gt;8.24%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&#13;&lt;/table&gt;&#13;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(h)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Accounts Receivable&lt;/b&gt; &amp;#150;&#13;We record bad debt expense based on historical write-offs combined with an evaluation of current conditions. The allowance for&#13;doubtful accounts was $0.6 million and $0.5 million at December 31, 2011 and 2010, respectively. Bad debt expense for the years&#13;ended December 31, 2011, 2010 and 2009 was $0.7 million, $0.6 million and $0.6 million, respectively. Receivables not expected&#13;to be received in 2012 are included as non-current assets in Operations and Developer Contracts Receivable.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(i)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Revenues&lt;/b&gt; - General metered&#13;customer&amp;#146;s bills for regulated water service are typically comprised of two components; a fixed service charge and a volumetric&#13;or consumption charge. Revenues from general metered service water customers, except Tidewater fixed service charges, include amounts&#13;billed in arrears on a cycle basis and unbilled amounts estimated from the last meter reading date to the end of the accounting&#13;period. The estimated unbilled amounts are determined by utilizing factors which include historical consumption usage and current&#13;climate and economic conditions. Actual billings may differ from our estimates. Tidewater customers are billed in advance for their&#13;fixed service charge and these revenues are recognized as the service is provided to the customer.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Southern Shores is an unmetered system. Customers&#13;are billed a fixed service charge in advance at the beginning of each month and revenues are recognized as earned.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;Revenues from the City of Perth Amboy management&#13;contract are comprised of fixed and variable fees. Fixed fees, which have been set for the life of the contract, are billed monthly&#13;and recorded as earned. Variable fees, which are not significant, are recorded upon approval of the amount by the City of Perth&#13;Amboy.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(j)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Deferred Charges and Other&#13;Assets&lt;/b&gt; - Unamortized Debt Expense is amortized over the lives of the related issues. Restricted Cash represents proceeds from&#13;loans entered into through state financing programs and is held in trusts. The proceeds are restricted for specific capital expenditures&#13;and debt service requirements.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(k)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Income Taxes&lt;/b&gt; - Middlesex&#13;files a consolidated federal income tax return for the Company and income taxes are allocated based on the separate return method.&#13;Investment tax credits have been deferred and are amortized over the estimated useful life of the related property. For more information&#13;on income taxes, see Note 3 &amp;#150; Income Taxes.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(l)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Statements of Cash Flows&lt;/b&gt;&#13;- For purposes of reporting cash flows, the Company considers all highly liquid investments with original maturity dates of three&#13;months or less to be cash equivalents. Cash and cash equivalents represent bank balances and money market funds with investments&#13;maturing in less than 90 days.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(m)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Use of Estimates&lt;/b&gt; - Conformity&#13;with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America requires management to make estimates and assumptions&#13;that affect the reported amounts in the financial statements. Actual results could differ from those estimates.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(n)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Recent Accounting Pronouncements&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fair Value Measurements and Disclosures&#13;&lt;/b&gt;- In May 2011, the Financial Accounting Standards Board (the FASB) issued Accounting Standards Update (ASU) 2011-04, which&#13;amends Accounting Standards Codification (ASC) 820, &lt;i&gt;Fair Value Measurements and Disclosure&lt;/i&gt; (ASC 820), to update guidance&#13;related to fair value measurements and disclosures as a step towards achieving convergence between generally accepted accounting&#13;principles and international financial reporting standards. ASU 2011-04 clarifies intent about application of existing fair value&#13;measurements and disclosures, changes certain requirements for fair value measurements and requires expanded disclosures. ASU&#13;2011-04 is effective for interim and annual periods beginning after December 15, 2011. Adoption of 2011-04 is not expected to&#13;have any impact on the Company&amp;#146;s results of operations, cash flows or financial position.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;In January 2010, the FASB issued ASU 2010-06, which amends ASC 820, to add new requirements for&#13;disclosures about transfers into and out of Levels 1 and 2 and separate disclosures about purchases, sales, issuances, and&#13;settlements relating to Level 3 measurements. ASU 2010-06 also clarifies existing fair value disclosures about the level of&#13;disaggregation and about inputs and valuation techniques used to measure fair value. Further, ASU 2010-06 amends guidance on&#13;employers&amp;#146; disclosures about postretirement benefit plan assets under ASC 715, &lt;i&gt;Compensation &amp;#150; Retirement&#13;Benefits&lt;/i&gt; to require that disclosures be provided by classes of assets instead of by major categories of assets.  Adoption&#13;of ASU 2010-06 had no impact on the Company&amp;#146;s results of operations, cash flows or financial position.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; background-color: white"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; background-color: white"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(o)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Regulatory Accounting&lt;/b&gt; - We&#13;maintain our books and records in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America. Middlesex&#13;and certain of its subsidiaries, which account for 90% of Operating Revenues and 98% of Total Assets, are subject to regulation&#13;in the state in which they operate. Those companies are required to maintain their accounts in accordance with regulatory authorities&amp;#146;&#13;rules and guidelines, which may differ from other authoritative accounting pronouncements. In those instances, the Company follows&#13;the guidance provided in ASC 980, &lt;i&gt;Regulated Operations&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;In accordance with ASC 980, &lt;i&gt;Regulated Operations&lt;/i&gt;,&#13;costs and obligations are deferred if it is probable that these items will be recognized for rate-making purposes in future rates.&#13;Accordingly, we have recorded costs and obligations, which will be amortized over various future periods. Any change in the assessment&#13;of the probability of rate-making treatment will require us to change the accounting treatment of the deferred item. We have no&#13;reason to believe any of the deferred items that are recorded will be treated differently by the regulators in the future. For&#13;additional information, see Note 2 &amp;#150; Rate and Regulatory Matters.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt/12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(p)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Postretirement Benefit Plans&lt;/b&gt;&#13;- We maintain a noncontributory defined benefit pension plan (Pension Plan) which covers substantially all active employees who&#13;were hired prior to March 31, 2007. In addition, the Company maintains an unfunded supplemental plan for its executive officers.&#13;The Company has a postretirement benefit plan other than pensions (Other Benefits Plan) for substantially all of its retired employees.&#13;Employees hired after March 31, 2007 are not eligible to participate in this plan. Coverage includes healthcare and life insurance.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;The Company&amp;#146;s costs for providing postretirement&#13;benefits are dependent upon numerous factors, including actual plan experience and assumptions of future experience. Postretirement&#13;benefit plan obligations and expense are determined based on investment performance, discount rates and various other demographic&#13;factors related to the population participating in the Company&amp;#146;s postretirement benefit plans, all of which can change significantly&#13;in future years. For more information on the Company&amp;#146;s Postretirement Benefit Plans, see Note 7 &amp;#150; Employee Benefit&#13;Plans.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(q)&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Recent Developments&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Investment in Ridgewood Green RME, LLC -&#13;&lt;/b&gt;Middlesex and NSU Ridgewood, LLC, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Natural Systems Utilities, LLC, formed a joint venture, Ridgewood&#13;Green RME, LLC, (Ridgewood Green), which entered into a 20-year public-private partnership with the Village of Ridgewood, New Jersey&#13;(Ridgewood) whereby Ridgewood Green will design, build, own and operate facilities to optimize the production of electricity at&#13;Ridgewood's municipal wastewater treatment plant. Operation of the facilities is expected to begin in the fourth quarter of 2012.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sunoco Logistics Partners L.P. Wastewater&#13;Treatment Facility Operating Agreement - &lt;/b&gt;USA has entered into an agreement with Sunoco Logistics Partners L.P. (Sunoco Logistics)&#13;to operate the Eagle Point Biological Wastewater Treatment Facility (Eagle Point) in Westville, New Jersey. USA will be responsible&#13;for the daily operation of the industrial wastewater treatment facility at Sunoco Logistics' refined products terminal at Eagle&#13;Point commencing in the first quarter of 2012.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:OrganizationConsolidationAndPresentationOfFinancialStatementsDisclosureAndSignificantAccountingPoliciesTextBlock>

    <MSEX:RateMattersTextBlock contextRef="From2011-01-01to2011-12-31">&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note 2 - Rate and Regulatory Matters&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Rate Matters&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Middlesex - &lt;/b&gt;In January 2012, Middlesex&#13;filed an application with the NJBPU seeking permission to increase its base rates by approximately $11.3 million per year. The&#13;request was made as a result of capital investments Middlesex has made, or has committed to make, as well as increased operations&#13;and maintenance costs. We cannot predict whether the NJBPU will ultimately approve, deny, or reduce the amount of the request.&#13;A decision by the NJBPU is not expected until the fourth quarter of 2012.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;In August 2011, Middlesex implemented a NJBPU&#13;approved Purchased Water Adjustment Clause (PWAC), which allows for the recovery of increased costs of $0.4 million to purchase&#13;untreated water from the New Jersey Water Supply Authority (NJWSA) and treated water from a non-affiliated regulated water utility.&#13;It is expected that the PWAC rate will reset to zero as part of the ultimate decision rendered in the aforementioned Middlesex&#13;base rate increase request.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;In March 2010, the NJBPU granted&#13;an increase in Middlesex&amp;#146;s annual operating revenues of 13.57%, or $7.8 million. The increase was  necessitated&#13;by increased costs, as well as to provide a return on invested capital in rate base of $180.3 million based on a return on&#13;equity of 10.30%.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tidewater &amp;#150; &lt;/b&gt;In September 2011,&#13;Tidewater filed an application with the DEPSC seeking permission to increase its base rates by approximately $6.9 million per year.&#13;The request was made as a result of capital investments Tidewater has made, or has committed to make, as well as increased operations&#13;and maintenance costs. We cannot predict whether the DEPSC will ultimately approve, deny, or reduce the amount of the request.&#13;A decision by the DEPSC is not expected until the second half of 2012. In connection with the base rate increase request, Tidewater&#13;implemented a DEPSC approved 10.49% interim rate increase, subject to refund, on November 15, 2011.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;A Distribution System Improvement Charge (DSIC)&#13;is a DEPSC approved rate-mechanism that allows water utilities to recover investment in non-revenue producing capital improvements&#13;to the water system between base rate proceedings. The following summarizes Tidewater&amp;#146;s approved DSIC rates from January&#13;1, 2011 through November 15, 2011, when Tidewater&amp;#146;s DSIC was set to 0.0% in connection with the aforementioned 10.49% interim&#13;rate increase:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="width: 40%; margin-left: 0; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;In September 2009, the DEPSC approved an overall&#13;14.95% or $3.0 million increase in Tidewater&amp;#146;s base rates. This rate increase approval is based on a 10.0% return on equity.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;TESI&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt; &lt;/i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;#150; &lt;/b&gt;In July 2011,&#13;TESI filed an application with the DEPSC seeking permission to increase its base rates by approximately $0.8 million per year.&#13;The request was made as a result of capital investments TESI has made, or has committed to make, as well as increased operations&#13;and maintenance costs. We cannot predict whether the DEPSC will ultimately approve, deny, or reduce the amount of the request.&#13;A decision by the DEPSC is not expected until mid 2012. In connection with the base rate increase request, TESI implemented a DEPSC&#13;approved 7.6% interim rate increase, subject to refund, on September 28, 2011.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Southern Shores&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt; &lt;/i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;#150; &lt;/b&gt;Effective&#13;June 1, 2011, the DEPSC approved a multi-year agreement for a phased-in base rate increase for Southern Shores.&amp;#160; This increase&#13;was made as a result of capital investment in the upgrade and renovation of Southern Shores&amp;#146; primary water treatment facilities,&#13;as well as by increased operating costs.&amp;#160; Under the terms of the agreement, which expires on June 30, 2020, Southern Shores&#13;also increased rates on January 1, 2012, and will do so on each successive January 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; through 2015, to generate approximately&#13;$0.1 million of additional revenue on an annual basis with each increase. Thereafter, rate increases, if any, cannot exceed the&#13;lesser of the regional Consumer Price Index or 3%.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;In accordance with the tariff established for&#13;Southern Shores, an annual rate increase of 8.9% was implemented in January 2012.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Twin Lakes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt; &lt;/i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;#150; &lt;/b&gt;In&#13;December 2011, Twin Lakes and the interveners in the Twin Lakes Rate Case reached a settlement that provided a $0.1 million,&#13;three-year phased-in base rate increase for Twin Lakes.&amp;#160; This increase was made as a result of capital investment in the&#13;upgrade and renovation of the Twin Lakes System, as well as by increased operating costs.&amp;#160; The settlement was approved&#13;by the PAPUC in March 2012.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Regulatory Matters&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;We have recorded certain costs as regulatory&#13;assets because we expect full recovery of, or are currently recovering, these costs in the rates we charge customers. These deferred&#13;costs have been excluded from rate base and, therefore, we are not earning a return on the unamortized balances. These items are&#13;detailed as follows:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;&#13;&lt;p style="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif;
